programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is taking a stroll around the Marsh when all of a sudden a giant “owl” falls from the sky. Fearing that the scary bird would devour him, Joe hides himself behind a big rock. Bartle Bee passes by and finds something wrong about this furious “owl”. After a close examination, he discovers that this is not a bird but a paper kite. To fly the kite, Joe slides down a slope to help the kite gain altitude. The kite soars into the sky, taking Joe along on an exciting flight. At first, the fact that he’s ten feet off the ground frightens Joe Croaker. But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble discover that Old Billy’s office smells bad. They decide to help him get rid of the awful smell. They try to collect some fresh clean air from a flower field with bottles, and bring the air to the office. However, it’s hard to tell whether the fragrance is really inside the bottles. So they decide to use balloons to collect the scent. However, a little hedgehog accidentally pops the balloons when he tries to help them. Old Billy sees them and tells them that the stinky smell will go away if they keep good ventilation in the office.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is frightened upon spying what he believes to be a monster strolling around the pond. He soon realizes that the “monster” is actually a duck, but can’t work out that it’s in fact a toy duck. Assuming that this Rubber Ducky of Death is scheming to occupy his place, Joe Croaker flips out and decides to teach it a good lesson. He bullies the Rubber Ducky of Death until Bartle Bee sweeps it away. Bartle Bee is determined to rescue what he too, sadly, sees as a real—if unresponsive—duck. Joe gives chase to the two runaways, and they tangle with each other. During the confrontation, Bartle Bee accidentally gives the air-filled toy duck a prick with his sting, causing it to deflate and fly away. Still in the dark, Bartle Bee blames the disappearance of the poor little “creature” on Joe Croaker.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds a balloon dinosaur among the grass. The frog has no idea what he has discovered and he really panics at this “dinosaur” that is many times his own size. Joe Croaker begins to attack the balloon with pebbles he picks up from the ground. One of the pebbles bounces off the balloon and hits Bartle Bee’s honey jar on the ground. Though Joe Croaker tells Bartle Bee that he has nothing to do with the broken honey jar, the bee is smart enough to figure it out by himself.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo eats up all the food Joe Croaker has obtained, which puts the latter into a violate passion. And his mockery about Joe Croaker’s inability to fly adds fuel to fire. The hot-air balloons floating in the sky inspire the frog, who then manages to put together one with all the parts he collects from the garbage can. Flying with the ill-made balloon, Joe Croaker grabs the food from Cosmo and endeavors to catch the fly. But the balloon is too slow for Cosmo, so Joe plays dead to bamboozle Cosmo, who falls for it and ends up being caught. Just at that moment, the candle in the balloon exhausts itself. Both Joe Croaker and Cosmo fall to the ground, where the frog resumes his chase after his little foe.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a roly-poly toy when he is trying to get some candy near a dumpster. It’s a big smiling face doll. But the frog has no knowledge of what he is facing. He sees the roly-poly as a potential threat to him and the Marsh. Joe Croaker challenges the toy and attempts to take it down. The frog fails and finally he uses a rope to tie the roly-poly toy up.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: As the dung balls keep piling up, McBroom finds himself short of energy to get his work done all by himself. At Bartle Bee’s suggestion, he puts up a recruitment ad to look for someone to help him. The handsome benefits offered on this job allure many insects over, including Hercules Beetle, Snout Beetle and Bartle Bee. To select the best out of the three candidates, McBroom put them on a series of tests where Hercules Beetle stands out to win the position as McBroom’s assistant. Much to McBroom’s disappointment, however, his employee turns out to be quite lazy. So he has to give Hercules Beetle the sack and send him home.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Hammer the ox is an excellent blacksmith in his village but he only makes weapons. The village head persuades him to sell them at Carrotown because the market there is much larger. Hammer follows his advice and heads for Carrotown. Along the road, the ox tries to promote his weapons to an lumberjack and a watermelon farmer but they all mistake him for a robber and are scared to death.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper are walking through the forest. Unexpectedly, two hedgehogs stand in their way and plan to plunder their valuables. Velvet Touch throws two darts to them, which annoys the two robbers. They contract their bodies into two spiky balls and roll toward her. To protect Velvet Touch, Trapper rushes over and hits them with a long stick. He puts on an awesome Kung Fu show and transforms into Mad Wolf. After Trapper realizes he has spilt the beans, he deliberately loses out to hedgehogs and surrenders to them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: At night, three animals make a campfire and sit down for a rest. Velvet Touch keeps commending Hammer upon his braveness and complains about Trapper’s cowardice. Velvet Touch thinks Hammer can serve as a good bodyguard and persuades him to go with them together the next day. Hammer accepts her invitation with alacrity. The next morning, they continue on their way. The rabbit suggests to perform juggling acts to attract villagers over and sell Hammer’s weapons to them. Others nod their appreciation.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Artisan, the richest rooster in the world, writes a piece of calligraphy. All the officials curry favor with Artisan and praise him for creating such a masterpiece. However, the truth is that Artisan is an illiterate and the so-called calligraphy is just his scrawled handwritings. Artisan strolls to the backyard of his palace and sees a kite flying in the sky. On a whim, he decides to make a peerless kite by himself. He orders his attendant to choose the most expensive materials.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Pink Racket & A Promising Flower
programme.desc: The cubs are playing badminton in the kindergarten. Herbert likes the pink racket. However, he overhears the others say the color pink is only for girls. So he does not dare to take the pink one, even though the one he uses is broken during the match. Then Old Billy joins them. The kids laugh at his floral shirt, but Old Billy doesn’t seem to care. Herbert understands he doesn’t need to pay too much attention to others’ opinions, and decides to use the pink racket.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: The cubs are rehearsing a show. At first, Babu acts well in his role. However, he becomes nervous when Warren and Luna-Loo come to watch the rehearsal. He forgets his lines, and can’t act. Babu thinks he didn’t practice enough but Luna-Loo thinks he has stage fright. He gives his role to Ernie Jo. Then Babu’s dad helps him to overcome his stage fright, and asks him to imagine the audience as fruits. At last, Babu doesn’t feel nervous anymore and acts well in the show.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Party at Violet’s & Got a Spare?
programme.desc: Violet invites her friends to her home, and has made proper arrangement. She thinks things will go smoothly. However, when her friends come to her house, they don’t want to follow her arrangements. They want to eat cakes and play with the ball. Violet doesn’t know what to do. Her father tells her that she should discuss with her friends about what to do. Violet listens to her friends’ opinions, and they all have fun.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. programme.desc: The Smurfs and Homnibus befriend an unfortunate boy who is forced to steal for his master. Soon, the evil thief is turned over to the magistrate and the boy is happy to live with Homnibus.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's been a few hundred years since Grandpa Smurf has seen this old toy... It was given to Papa Smurf long, long ago and he does not remember what it does. But Baby Smurf does know that it brings surprises for everyone!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs' 200-year streak of good luck comes to an abrupt end when Gargamel finds Lady Luck's castle and, after locking her up in a dungeon, proceeds to tamper with her wheel of Fortune. Will the Smurfs remain inactive in the face of such ill luck ?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy shows his lack of maternal instinct when a lost baby bird adopts him as a mother and Greedy finds himself in the opposite situation... The Smurfs try to escape prehistoric times.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy brings a Fuzzle back to the Smurf village where the tiny, loveable creature multiplies and threatens to eat the new dam. Harmony plays his music and the entranced Fuzzles march back into the woods where they attach themselves to an unsuspecting Gargamel.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It had to happen to Brainy. The paragon of Smurfy etiquette, the epitome of correctness, the embodiment of all that is, let's face it, boring and pretentious, Brainy Smurf himself suffers the agony of becoming... say, different. But he is in grave danger...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel wants to create a monster. A horrible, gigantic creature, an awesome being that is going to destroy all the Smurfs! But Gargamel makes a slight mistake, and the result is going to astonish him and his cat Azrael.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the Smurfs reach Ancient China, they learn that the child Emperor is in danger of being deposed, and by whom? By the evil Garg-Fu-Yun, who wants to rule in the child's stead!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: No one believes Grandpa Smurf when he tells of far-away jungles and savannahs teeming with wild giant cats, striped horses, long-necked leaf-eaters and strange tribes... Only some Smurflings give some credit to his tales. But when Grandpa Smurf hears the sound of the magic Royal Drum in the forest, the one that can tame wild beasts, he sets out to prove that he's not an old addle-brained storyteller.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Allura the Enchantress possesses a very special magic orb whose energy, as she says, can lift spirits and inspire the uninspired! All you have to do is hold the orb between your hands... It is true the orb bestows inspiration, up to a point. But its side effects can be very dangerous, as the Smurfs find out when they become addicted to it...

programme.title: Handy's Window-Vision
programme.desc: Miner Smurf leaves no stone unturned and this is how he discovers a crystal that transmits images. Thus Handy is able to invent window-vision and, every morning from then on, the Smurfs are able to watch Hefty's workouts, Farmer Smurf's crop reports or even the Brainy Smurf Hour. But would you believe it? The evil wizard Gargamel takes advantage of this image-watching to catch Smurfs!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In his search for something new, Vanity dons a Gargamel-made magic hat that transforms his face into a mess. Through trickery, Papa Smurf gets the antidote from the wicked wizard and once more, Vanity is beautiful.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Little Sickly turns into a hero when he forgets his ailments and saves the rest of the Smurfs from the deadly forget-me flowers.

programme.title: No Time For Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy, Brainy, Clumsy, and Smurfette discover the hourglass of time in a cave and due to their bungling, time spins erratically out of control for all of the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grandpa has never acted his age, but here he is, younger than ever, after having been touched by the water of the Fountain of Youth. Sassette will have to watch the 1000-year-old kid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs arrive in Camelot to witness several events: treacherous Morgan Le Fay steals Excalibur, the magic sword, and turns Merlin the Wizard, King Arthur and Lancelot into helpless victims.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Spring has the Smurfs all competing for Smurfette's affection and Gargamel decides to put a spell on her to help him capture the Smurfs. Papa Smurf intervenes and with the help of the foolish Azrael he foils the wizard's plans.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wonderful joy of Christmas for Baby Smurf and everyone else is almost ruined by the evil Chlorhydris who puts a spell on Mr. Nicholas to stop him from spreading holiday cheer. Fortunately, Papa Smurf and his little blue creatures break the spell and Christmas spreads over the land once more.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Posing for a sculpture, especially a huge composition like that of Painter Smurf, is very tiring work, and you can't help moving a little. Now Papa Smurf finds a way to keep the posers perfectly still. There are drawbacks though, as the Smurfs will soon realise...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: What a strange stone Clumsy has unearthed! In it, he can see events that are going to happen... Yet knowing part of the future sometimes brings bad luck!

programme.title: Jokey's Medecine
programme.desc: Because of Jokey's pranks, none of the Smurfs believe him when he tells them that Azrael the cat is ready to pounce on them. Feeling guilty and responsible, he hurries to Gargamel's castle and plays some explosive jokes on the wizard and his cat so he can free his friends.

programme.title: Smurfette's Lucky Star
programme.desc: Smurfette has chosen her lucky wishing star and it will remain hers forever... as long as she wishes for unselfish things. But Smurfette, with her badly chosen wishes, makes her star fall from the sky and Gargamel wants it...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: The Magic Sack Of Mr Nicholas
programme.desc: If there is one thing that displeases the evil enchantress Chlorhydris, it's the mirth and love of Christmas. She sets out to kidnap Mr. Nicholas' magic sack, the one in which he carries all the toys that good children receive at Christmas. She doesn't know that a frowning Grouchy Smurf is hiding inside the sack.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Smurf A Mile In My Shoes
programme.desc: The Smurfs band together to retrieve a sea-shell they need to release a hermit imp from the Sea Witch, as she cursed him with ugliness and a language very few understand. The Smurfs return with the sea-shell in time to break the curse and return the hermit to the handsome imp he once was.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: For a long time, Gargamel has been trying to make gold out of Smurfs. This time, he succeeds... Three Smurfs are changed into gold coins! Can Papa Smurf change them back again? And where are they? Not in Gargamel's hovel, for two thieves have taken his precious coins from him!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh dear! Sassette has lost a tooth. Papa Smurf explains that if she puts her tooth under her pillow, the Mouse Fairy will bring her a present in the morning. But the next morning there is no present under the pillow. The Mouse Fairy has not been. She has been captured in one of Gargamel’s Smurf traps. And now the evil wizard is concocting a dreadful plan.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: We all know Grouchy Smurf hates a lot of things. But one thing he hates more than anything else is water, when there is enough of it to drown in. You see, Grouchy can't swim. And when the Smurfs notice this peculiarity and try to teach him how to survive in water, the evil wizard Gargamel makes things a little more dangerous than they ought to be....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel infects Hefty's heart with hate and then uses the little Smurf as a decoy for the others. Fortunately, Hefty's love overcomes his hate and he helps his little friends escape from Gargamel's clutches.

programme.title: Alarming Smurfs
programme.desc: Feeling unwanted, the Smurflings run away. They take things to remind them of home, so the Smurfs think there's a thief in their midst. programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In old Mesopotamia, after Smurfette pricks her thumb on the thorn of a magic flower, anything she touches turns into a plant. Can Papa save her from the evil flowers of Babble-on?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Being Papa Smurf has its share of joys but also a few disadvantages. Such as being interrupted every five minutes, even when in the middle of delicate magic experiments. So Papa wonders if it's not possible to be replaced by a decision-taking Smurf...

programme.title: The Horn Of Plenty
programme.desc: Mother Nature always does her best, but this time she's gone wrong. Her wand gets the wrong results and she accidentally damages the Autumn harvest. Now the Smurfs and all the forest animals face a lean and hungry winter. The only place where the Smurfs could get food would be the Land of Plenty. But Gargamel steals the famed Horn of Plenty to lure the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is the dramatic, moving story of the friendship between Smurfette and her pet mouse. A sad event reduces Smurfette to tears... Can the Smurfs comfort the despairing Smurfette?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfette leads the Smurflings on a nature hike, but Puppy gets too far ahead and they chase him into the land of the Wartmongers. King Bullrush captures them in bubbles and imprisons them. A group of rebels rescue the Smurflings and they escape on the back of Puppy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel's theft of the Fairies' gold almost brings a state of war between the Fairies and the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wizard Gargamel creates an enticing Smurfette to lure the Smurfs into his castle. The Smurfette is thoroughly entranced with the little Smurfs, becomes one of them and together they cause Gargamel's wicked plan to backfire on him. With a magic spell Papa Smurf finally succeeds in making Smurfette look more Smurflike. It is no longer possible for Gargamel to dictate his evil orders through her powder box's mirror.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A war is raging in the Middle Ages. Knights in armor in hot pursuit inadvertently destroy the Smurfs Village so a small band of Smurfs decide to avenge this wrongdoing. Won't Papa Smurf think this is too human-like a reaction?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy Smurf has saved Clumsy from a horrible fate. Clumsy swears eternal devotion to his savior and does his best to repay his debt... With awkward results. A clever scheme is needed to stop Clumsy's well-meant catastrophes...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: How can the Smurfs save this future baby vulture? Right now, it's still in the egg and they must find a way of incubating the bird. And it just happens that the evil wizard Gargamel has found a way of changing himself into a bird to get at the Smurfs...

programme.title: It Came From Outer Smurf
programme.desc: Dreamy wants to encounter beings from outer space so much that no one believes him when he talks of having met one. Yet the arrival of this extraterrestrial is going to wreak havoc in the Smurf Village...

programme.title: All Creatures Great And Smurf
programme.desc: Nat Smurf is convinced he can help all creatures with his healing ways, even the wicked Azrael after he gets his paw caught in a trap. He heals well, but even though he is tempted to stay with the Smurfs, he runs back to Gargamel while leading his old master away from Smurf Village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: While out on a mischief-making mission to destroy the Smurfs' Happy Halloween party, Gargamel and Hogatha catch Lazy who has been accidentally turned red by Mother Nature. Papa and the Smurfs help Lazy escape while Mother Nature has Father Time help turn Lazy's red into blue just in time for the Halloween party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Despite Grandpa's warning that it is wrong to take wild animals away from their habitat, the Smurflings, back from a long trip in the magic balloon, bring along a Nebbit, a funny, loveable creature. Funny and loveable for a little while, but then matters get more complex...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs arrive in Camelot to witness several events: treacherous Morgan Le Fay steals Excalibur, the magic sword, and turns Merlin the Wizard, King Arthur and Lancelot into helpless victims.

programme.title: The Bad Place
programme.desc: What is this little moon coming from above? Why, it's a crater-pockmarked globe of mud inhabited by the Grimeys, a family of mud-splattering, mud-eating creatures from out there in the sky. Not all the Smurfs are enthusiastic about the visitors....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In the times of Greek antiquity, a spoiled heiress meets Smurfette and believes she's the most beautiful doll she has ever seen. To save Smurfette, Papa Smurf resorts to an old trick...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Journey To The Centre Of The Smurf
programme.desc: Winter is setting in on the Village of the Smurfs. The little Smurfs are freezing. But what is Clumsy doing with this strange rock he's discovered? And why is Miner Smurf so enthusiastic about their new discovery? Surely, one more addition to Clumsy's rock collection is not worth all this hoopla... The Smurfs will discover danger and surprises when they go underground.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy Smurf has hit on a revolutionary new idea: a sort of smurfless carriage that moves on railroad tracks. He calls it a railsmurfer and it makes for less work in the Village... until Gargamel chances upon it.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs arrive in Camelot to witness several events: treacherous Morgan Le Fay steals Excalibur, the magic sword, and turns Merlin the Wizard, King Arthur and Lancelot into helpless victims.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wizard Gargamel creates an enticing Smurfette to lure the Smurfs into his castle. The Smurfette is thoroughly entranced with the little Smurfs, becomes one of them and together they cause Gargamel's wicked plan to backfire on him. With a magic spell Papa Smurf finally succeeds in making Smurfette look more Smurflike. It is no longer possible for Gargamel to dictate his evil orders through her powder box's mirror.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy has built a very complex Smurf machine that does everything. It proves dangerous when it nearly destroys the village, but comes in useful when, with the help of the other Smurfs, it saves the young prince Gerard's kingdom from the queen aunt Imperia's dastardly intentions.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: There are few things Grandpa Smurf enjoys more than telling a good scary story, and there are few Smurfs who don't love to listen. But things get a little too much for Brainy Smurf when Grandpa tells of Poltersmurfs, and Poltersmurfs begin harrowing Brainy...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel wants to create a monster. A horrible, gigantic creature, an awesome being that is going to destroy all the Smurfs! But Gargamel makes a slight mistake, and the result is going to astonish him and his cat Azrael.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's been a few hundred years since Grandpa Smurf has seen this old toy... It was given to Papa Smurf long, long ago and he does not remember what it does. But Baby Smurf does know that it brings surprises for everyone!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Being Papa Smurf has its share of joys but also a few disadvantages. Such as being interrupted every five minutes, even when in the middle of delicate magic experiments. So Papa wonders if it's not possible to be replaced by a decision-taking Smurf...

programme.title: The Magic Stick
programme.desc: With a borrowed recipe from Homnibus, Papa Smurf creates a magic stick that Clumsy takes and loses in the woods. Soon after, Bigmouth comes for a visit and before he eats all the smurfberries, Papa Smurf finds the magic stick and whisks the giant away.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: All The News That's Fit To Smurf
programme.desc: Curious Smurf has an idea: why not print a sheet with all the Village news? He's sure to interest all his readers of the Smurf Tattler. But things don't go exactly to plan when Papa finds super smurfberries.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha, the repulsive witch, captures the Smurfette. She wants to steal from the little blue beauty her golden hair. Can the Smurfs save their little female companion before it is too late? Can Hogatha grow hair like Smurfette's?

programme.title: Brainy Smurf, Friend To All Animals
programme.desc: Brainy dons his safari hat and roams the forest to do good deeds for animals. He mostly gives advice to the creatures but balks when he can really save the life of a wildcat being hunted by Gargamel. Nat gives Brainy the courage to free the cat from Gargamel's trap.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In Egypt there is a cat pharaoh called Azrael and the name rings a bell with the Smurfs. As does the cruel taskmaster's name! Gargahotep wants to enslave the Smurfs to build a pyramid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Dreamy's wish of becoming an Astrosmurf comes true when Papa Smurf puts him to sleep, magically transforming the landscape and the Smurfs into a space fantasy. Gargamel keeps a close watch on their antics through his crystal ball, but he too falls victim to Papa Smurf's magic and is sent into a thunderstorm.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy Smurf's misadventures take him across a river into Pussywillow Hollow. There he meets the Pixies – charming and shapely beings whose enemies, the Wartmongers, will meet the Smurfs in some unforeseen ways.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf's done it again. This time, in front of Papa Smurf, too. He has recited a spell that changes everything to stone. Everything including himself and all the Smurfs and the Village, and the forest around for miles... Fortunately, Peewit appears....

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The village of the Smurfs used to live without a clock. But now suddenly time becomes a precious commodity and Brainy Smurf designs a schedule to take advantage of the new Village clock... Can the Smurfs survive the attacks of time?

programme.title: Vanity Fair
programme.desc: Gargamel's magic mirror traps Vanity Smurf inside it so Smurfette and Brainy rush to his rescue. Once inside the mirror-world, they cause a giant explosion that shatters the glassy enclosure and hurry back to their smurfy village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Sweepy the chimney sweep Smurf is not the most popular inhabitant of the Village of the Smurfs. He is rather messy, and the clouds of soot that he makes certainly don't add to his popularity. Only the Smurflings find him great company as he's the only one who can get dirty and not be told off. Yet in their enthusiasm for Sweepy, the Smurflings endanger the Village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh, sure, kickball (or smurfball, as they call it) is all right for a while. But it gets sort of boring after a few centuries. Now there's this new game that has been invented by a nondescript Smurf, a game where you hit a ball with a stick and send it into a gopher hole...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurf Friendship Day is that time in the year when, more than ever, the Smurfs show friendliness to one another. But won't Chlorhydris destroy those good feelings? And how can the Smurfs find a way to exchange Cupid's arrows for something nicer?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Snappy and Nat steal Gargamel's formula to make another Smurf – a female to be a companion to Smurfette. They create Sassette, who causes mischief wherever she goes. Papa uses his Smurfiness Solution to turn Gargamel's evil Sassette into a playful Smurfy Sassette.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Get up early in the morning, before any other Smurf is out of bed, to prepare a scrumptious Smurfberry muffin. Spend all morning on preparing Smurf delicacies for lunch. Than all afternoon to have dinner ready – and delicious – on time. And do you get so much as a thank you form the Smurfs? So Greedy Smurf quits. The Village is in trouble... And soon, so is Greedy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfs try to avoid contact with humans. But this time, Sassette is happy to be friends with a little witch called Melina, whose spells often end up in disaster. And anyway, are witches really human? At any rate, wizards such as Gargamel are.

programme.title: Secret Of The Village Well
programme.desc: Why is Clumsy Smurf waiting day and night near the Village well? What is the wish that he wants to be kept secret? How is Gargamel going to be mixed up in this mysterious affair? Is Gargamel going to catch the Smurfs at last?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Harmony unwittingly signs a contract with Ghost Writer for a symphony that imprisons him in a ghostly nightclub for life! Papa Smurf demands a jury trial with ghostly jurors and a judge that finds Harmony innocent and Ghost Writer guilty of plagiarism.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Once in a blue moon, as the legend goes, a baby Smurf is delivered to the Smurfs and everyone in the village becomes attached to the new arrival. But a mistake has been made and the stork returns to take the baby back. Grouchy and Smurfette have become so attached to the baby that the baby is returned.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A fierce wind carries the Smurfs' windmill away, with several Smurfs inside. Is Lazy Smurf really at fault or is an injustice being committed? Are the captive Smurfs going to be saved from the volcano's crater? Is Brainy going to smurf up his mouth for a moment?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs' theatrical production of 'Robin Smurf' comes to life as the legendary hero is portrayed by a really good actor...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La reina Agripina no dejara que su hijo, el principe Godofredo, se case con la dulce Priscila. Ella quiere como nuera a una chica que sea capaz de mostrarle algo que nunca antes haya visto. Cuando Hogata se entera y descubre la existencia de Abuelo Pitufo, esta segura de que lograra sorprender a la reina con su captura. Por supuesto, Hogata debe atrapar primero a Abuelo Pitufo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo llevaba algunos cientos de anos sin ver su antiguo juguete. Se lo entregaron a Papa Pitufo hace mucho tiempo y no recuerda exactamente como funciona. ¡Pero Bebe Pitufo sabe que tiene sorpresas para todos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La racha de 200 anos de buena suerte de los Pitufos se interrumpe bruscamente cuando Gargamel encuentra el castillo de la Dama de la Fortuna, la encierra en una mazmorra y comienza a manipular su rueda de la suerte. ¿Se quedaran de brazos cruzados los Pitufos ante ese cambio de fortuna?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Como se puede devolver un bebe triceratops a sus padres? Los Pitufos estan haciendo todo lo que pueden, esquivando dinosaurios y misteriosos seres que viven en cuevas prehistoricas...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Tontin lleva una Rebotilla al pueblo, donde la pequena y adorable criatura se multiplicara y amenazara con comerse la nueva presa. Pitufo Armonia toca una cancion y las Rebotillas encandiladas le siguen en fila india hasta el bosque donde se juntaran a Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Tenia que pasarle a Pitufo Filosofo. La quintaesencia de la pitufietiqueta, el epitome de la correccion, la personificacion de todas esas virtudes es, asumamoslo, aburrido y pretencioso. Y ahora, Pitufo Filosofo sufre la agonia de volverse... digamos que diferente. Sin embargo, esta en grave peligro...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel quiere crear un monstruo. Una criatura horrible y gigantesca, ¡un ser imponente que destruya a todos los Pitufos! Pero Gargamel comete un pequeno error y el resultado les dejara asombrados a su gato Azrael y a el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a la antigua China, descubren que el emperador nino corre peligro de ser depuesto. ¿Y por quien? ¡Por el malvado Garg-Fu-Yun, que quiere hacerse con el trono del nino!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Nadie le cree al Abuelo Pitufo cuando habla de junglas y sabanas lejanas, repletas de gatos salvajes gigantes, caballos a rayas, comedores de hojas de cuello largo y extranas tribus... Tan solo algunos Pitufitos dan cierto credito a sus historias. Pero, cuando Abuelo Pitufo escucha en el bosque el sonido del tambor real magico, un instrumento capaz de domar bestias salvajes, se lanza a la aventura para demostrar que no es un contador de historias al que el cerebro le juega malas pasadas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La encantadora Allura posee una esfera magica muy especial cuya energia, segun ella misma dice, puede levantar el animo e inspirar a aquellos faltos de inspiracion. Todo lo que hay que hacer es sostener la esfera con las manos... Es cierto que la esfera fomenta la inspiracion, pero solo hasta cierto punto. Sin embargo, sus efectos secundarios pueden ser muy peligrosos, tal como descubren los Pitufos cuando se hacen adictos a la esfera...

programme.title: La Pitufivision De Genio
programme.desc: Pitufo Minero rebusca bajo todas las piedras y, gracias a ello, descubre un cristal que transmite imagenes. Esto permite a Pitufo Carpintero inventar la pitufivision y, desde ese momento, los Pitufos pueden ver todas las mananas los entrenamientos de Pitufo Fortachon, los informes de las cosechas de Pitufo Labrador e incluso el programa de Pitufo Filosofo. Pero ¿quien podria haberlo imaginado? ¡El malvado mago Gargamel se aprovecha de la pitufivision para atrapar Pitufos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En su busqueda de algo novedoso, Pitufo Vanidoso se pone un sombrero magico creado por Gargamel que le deja la cara hecha un adefesio. Mediante una argucia, Papa Pitufo consigue robarle el antidoto al malvado mago, logrando asi que Pitufo Vanidoso recupere su belleza.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Enfermizo se convierte en un heroe cuando se olvida de sus dolencias y salva al resto de los Pitufos de las peligrosas flores del olvido.

programme.title: Poema Al Tiempo
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero, Pitufo Filosofo, Pitufo Torpe y Pitufina descubren el reloj de arena del tiempo en una cueva y empiezan a trastear con el, lo que provoca que el tiempo se descontrole para todos los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo nunca habia aparentado su edad, pero ahora esta mas joven que nunca tras haber entrado en contacto con el agua de la Fuente de la Juventud. Sasita tendra que cuidar de este nino milenario...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llegan a Camelot, donde presencian varios sucesos: la traicionera Morgana Le Fey roba Excalibur, la espada magica, y transforma al mago Merlin, al rey Arturo y a Lancelot en indefensas victimas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La primavera provoca que todos los Pitufos esten compitiendo por el amor de Pitufina y Gargamel decide hechizarla para que le ayuda a capturarlos. Papa Pitufo toma cartas en el asunto y con la ayuda del despistado gato Azrael consigue darle la vuelta al plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Navidad De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: La ilusion de Navidad se ve frustrada cuando Chlorhydris hechiza a San Nicolas para que no pueda repartir felicidad en Navidad. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo y los demas pitufos consiguen romper el hechizo y devolver la Navidad a su bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Posar para una escultura, sobre todo para una composicion enorme como la de Pitufo Pintor, es un trabajo agotador, y es imposible evitar moverse un poco. Ahora, Papa Pitufo ha encontrado la forma de que los modelos se queden completamente quietos. Sin embargo, tiene algunos inconvenientes, tal como los Pitufos comprobaran pronto...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Pitufo Torpe ha desenterrado una extrana piedra! En ella, puede ver los eventos que van a suceder... ¡No obstante, conocer parte del futuro a veces trae mala suerte!

programme.title: Medicina Para Bromista
programme.desc: Por culpa de todas las bromas que gasta Pitufo Bromista, ningun Pitufo le cree cuando les avisa de que el gato Azrael esta a punto de atacarlos. Como se siente culpable, se dirige al castillo de Gargamel y le gasta unas cuantas bromas muy explosivas al mago y a su gato para poder liberar a sus amigos.

programme.title: La Estrella De La Suerte De Pitufina
programme.desc: Pitufina ha elegido su estrella de los deseos de la suerte y sera suya para siempre... mientras formule deseos que no sean egoistas. Pero Pitufina, con sus malas elecciones a la hora de hacer deseos, provoca que la estrella caiga del cielo y Gargamel quiere hacerse con ella...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Costal Magico De Santa Claus
programme.desc: Si hay algo que desagrada a la malvada hechicera Clorhidris es la bondad y el amor propios de la Navidad. Trama un plan para robar el costal magico de Santa Claus, en el que transporta todos los juguetes que los ninos que se han portado bien reciben por Navidad. Sin embargo, no sabe que un enfurrunado Pitufo Grunon esta escondido dentro del saco.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos se preparan para recuperar una concha marina que necesitan para liberar a un ermitano de las garras de la Bruja del Mar, la cual la maldijo con un aspecto horrible y un lenguaje dificil de entender. Los Pitufos consiguen recuperar la concha a tiempo para romper el maleficio y devolver al ermitano a su verdadero ser.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel lleva mucho tiempo intentando obtener oro a partir de los Pitufos. Esta vez, lo ha conseguido: ¡ha transformado a tres Pitufos en monedas de oro! ¿Conseguira Papa Pitufo devolverles su forma original? Pero ¿donde estan? No estan en la choza de Gargamel, ¡y es que dos ladrones le han robado sus preciosas monedas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Madre mia! A Sasita se le ha caido un diente. Papa Pitufo le explica que, si coloca el diente bajo la almohada, encontrara un obsequio del hada de los dientes al dia siguiente. Sin embargo, a la manana siguiente no hay ningun regalo debajo de la almohada. El hada de los dientes no ha acudido. Resulta que esta atrapada en una de las trampas de Gargamel. Y ahora, el malvado mago esta tramando un terrible plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos sabemos que Pitufo Grunon odia varias cosas. Pero la cosa que odia mas que nada es el agua, cuando hay suficiente para que se pueda ahogar. Pitufo Grunon no sabe nadar. Y cuando los Pitufos notan esto y le tratan de ensenar como sobrevivir en el agua, el malvado mago Gargamel hace que todo sea un poco mas peligroso de lo que deberia ser...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel infecta de odio el corazon de Pitufo Fortachon y, a continuacion, usa al pequeno Pitufo como senuelo para los demas. Afortunadamente, el amor de Pitufo Fortachon vence al odio y ayuda a sus pequenos amigos a escapar de las garras de Gargamel.

programme.title: ¡alarma, Pitufos!
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos se sienten poco queridos y deciden huir. Se llevan consigo objetos que les recuerden su hogar, lo que hace que los Pitufos crean que hay un ladron entre ellos. Pitufo Filosofo intenta atrapar al ladron instalando pitufialarmas. Las alarmas provocan un estruendo que atrae a los Pitufitos de vuelta a casa, donde Papa Pitufo les convence de que los quieren.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En la antigua Mesopotamia, despues de que Pitufina se pinche en el dedo con la espina de una flor magica, todo lo que toca se transforma en una planta. ¿Podra Papa Pitufo salvarla de las malvadas flores de Babilonia?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Ser Papa Pitufo da muchas alegrias, pero tambien tiene algunas desventajas. Por ejemplo, que alguien te interrumpa cada cinco minutos, incluso cuando estas en medio de delicados experimentos magicos. Eso hace que Papa Pitufo se plantee si seria posible que un Pitufo le sustituyera y se encargara de tomar las decisiones...

programme.title: El Cuerno De La Abundancia
programme.desc: Madre Naturaleza siempre da lo mejor de si misma, pero esta vez algo ha salido mal. Su varita no funciona segun lo previsto y dana por accidente la cosecha otonal. Ahora, los Pitufos y todos los animales del bosque se enfrentan a la escasez y el hambre de cara al invierno. El unico lugar donde los Pitufos podrian obtener comida seria la Tierra de la Abundancia. Sin embargo, Gargamel roba el famoso Cuerno de la Abundancia para tender una trampa a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una aventura dramatica y conmovedora... Pitufina y su mascota Re chillido. La pequena Pitufina esta inundada en lagrimas. ¿Podran los demas pitufos consolarla?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufina guia a los Pitufos de caminata por la naturaleza, pero Puppy se adelanto demasiado y tras perseguirlo acaban en el territorio de los Wartmongers. El Rey de los Wartmongers acaba haciendoles prisioneros en burbujas, pero un grupo de rebeldes les rescata y consiguen huir a lomos de Puppy.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Todo Esta Bien Si Termina Bien
programme.desc: El robo del oro de las hadas por parte de Gargamel casi lleva a la guerra a los Pitufos con las hadas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Se ha desatado una guerra en la Edad Media. Unos caballeros vestidos con armadura destrozan por accidente la Aldea Pitufa, lo que provoca que una pequena banda de Pitufos decida vengar esta afrenta. ¿No pensara Papa Pitufo que esta es una accion demasiado propia de los humanos?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero ha salvado a Pitufo Torpe de un terrible destino. Pitufo Torpe jura devocion eterna a su salvador y se esfuerza al maximo por saldar su deuda... con consecuencias desastrosas. Se hace necesario idear un plan ingenioso para evitar las bienintencionadas catastrofes causadas por Pitufo Torpe...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Falso Y El Feo Plumaje
programme.desc: ¿Que pueden hacer los Pitufos para salvar a este futuro pollo de buitre? Ahora mismo, aun esta en el huevo y deben encontrar la forma de incubarlo. Y sucede que el malvado mago Gargamel ha encontrado una forma de transformarse en un ave para acercarse a los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Sonador desea encontrar vida extraterrestre pero en la Aldea se burlan de el. Nadie le creera cuando les diga que ha hablado con un ser de otro planeta.

programme.title: A Todas Las Criaturas Grandes Y Pequenas
programme.desc: Pitufo Natural esta convencido de que puede ayudar a todas las criaturas con sus dones curativos, incluso al malvado Azrael, cuya pata queda atrapada en una trampa. El gato se cura y, a pesar de que tiene la tentacion de quedarse con los Pitufos, regresa con Gargamel, pero conduce a su dueno hacia un lugar alejado de la Aldea Pitufa.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Durante una mision para interrumpir la fiesta de Halloween de los Pitufos, Gargamel y Hogatha consiguen capturar a Perezoso, el cual se ha vuelto rojo por un extrano capricho de la naturaleza. Papa Pitufo y los demas conseguiran liberar a Perezoso, y la Madre Naturaleza devolvera su color al pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: A pesar de que Abuelo Pitufo les advierte de que no es bueno sacar a los animales silvestres de su habitat, los Pitufitos, que regresan de un largo viaje en el globo magico, traen con ellos a Nebbit, una divertida y adorable criatura. Y, aunque es divertida y adorable por un tiempo, entonces las cosas se complican...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llegan a Camelot, donde presencian varios sucesos: la traicionera Morgana Le Fey roba Excalibur, la espada magica, y transforma al mago Merlin, al rey Arturo y a Lancelot en indefensas victimas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que es esa pequena luna que ha llegado del cielo? Es un globo de barro cubierto de crateres y habitado por los Lodosos, una familia de criaturas que vienen del cielo y comen y salpican barro. No todos los Pitufos demuestran entusiasmo por los visitantes...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En tiempos de la antigua Grecia, una malcriada heredera se encuentra con Pitufina y cree que es la muneca mas bonita que ha visto jamas. Para salvar a Pitufina, Papa Pitufo recurre a una vieja treta...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Viaje Al Pitufo De La Tierra
programme.desc: El invierno ha llegado a la Aldea Pitufa. Y los pequenos Pitufos estan helados de frio. ¿Pero que esta haciendo Pitufo Torpe con esa extrana roca que ha descubierto? ¿Y por que esta tan entusiasmado Pitufo Minero con su nuevo descubrimiento? Nadie entiende a que se debe tanto revuelo por una simple nueva roca para la coleccion de Pitufo Torpe... Al adentrarse bajo tierra, los Pitufos encontraran peligros y sorpresas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero ha tenido una nueva y revolucionaria idea: una especie de carro que se mueve sobre railes y no requiere que los Pitufos tiren de el. Lo llama pitufitren y hace que la vida en la aldea resulte menos cansada... hasta que Gargamel lo descubre.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llegan a Camelot, donde presencian varios sucesos: la traicionera Morgana Le Fey roba Excalibur, la espada magica, y transforma al mago Merlin, al rey Arturo y a Lancelot en indefensas victimas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa a Pituforobotin para que ayude a todos los Pitufos en sus labores, pero Filosofo lo reprograma para que abandone la Aldea Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una de las cosas con las que mas disfruta Abuelo Pitufo es contar una buena historia de miedo, y a la mayoria de los Pitufos les encantan. Sin embargo, las cosas se complican para Pitufo Filosofo cuando Abuelo Pitufo habla de las pitufianimas y estas comienzan a acecharle...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel quiere crear un monstruo. Una criatura horrible y gigantesca, ¡un ser imponente que destruya a todos los Pitufos! Pero Gargamel comete un pequeno error y el resultado les dejara asombrados a su gato Azrael y a el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo llevaba algunos cientos de anos sin ver su antiguo juguete. Se lo entregaron a Papa Pitufo hace mucho tiempo y no recuerda exactamente como funciona. ¡Pero Bebe Pitufo sabe que tiene sorpresas para todos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Ser Papa Pitufo da muchas alegrias, pero tambien tiene algunas desventajas. Por ejemplo, que alguien te interrumpa cada cinco minutos, incluso cuando estas en medio de delicados experimentos magicos. Eso hace que Papa Pitufo se plantee si seria posible que un Pitufo le sustituyera y se encargara de tomar las decisiones...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Con una receta que le presto Omnibus, Papa Pitufo crea una varita magica que Pitufo Torpe se lleva y pierde en el bosque. Poco despues, reciben la visita de Giganton y, antes de que pueda comerse todas las pitufrutas, Papa Pitufo encuentra la varita magica y lo aleja.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Curioso ha tenido una idea: ¿por que no imprimir un boletin con todas las noticias de la aldea? Esta seguro de que sus cotilleos sobre los Pitufos interesaran a todos los lectores. Pero las cosas no salen exactamente segun lo previsto cuando Papa Pitufo encuentra superpitufrutas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La repulsiva bruja Hogata captura a Pitufina. Quiere robarle a la pequena belleza azul su cabello dorado. ¿Conseguiran salvar los Pitufos a su pequena companera antes de que sea demasiado tarde? ¿Lograra Hogata una cabellera como la de Pitufina?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel y Baltasar se ponen a los mandos de un Robotin gigante para obligar al rey Gerard a que les entregue a Pitufo Robotin. Cuando el Robotin esta a punto de destruir el castillo, Giganton, el nuevo, enorme y extrano amigo de Pitufo Robotin, vence al Robotin. Pitufo Robotin sufre danos durante la batalla, pero Pitufo Carpintero lo arregla y le implanta una caja de voz que le permite decir «¡Hola!».

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En Egipto hay un faraon gato llamado Azrael, un nombre que resulta familiar a los Pitufos. ¡Y lo mismo sucede con el nombre del cruel capataz! Gargahotep quiere esclavizar a los Pitufos para construir una piramide...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador vera cumplido su deseo de ser un Astropitufo cuando Papa Pitufo le hechiza para quedarse dormido, transformando el paisaje y a los Pitufos en una fantasia galactica. Gargamel vigila de cerca las travesuras de los Pitufos desde su bola de cristal, pero el hechizo de Papa Pitufo tambien tiene efecto en el y le transporta hasta el centro de una tormenta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Patoso y sus desventuras le llevan a traves de un rio a un lugar desconocido. Alli conoce a las duendecillas, unas adorables criaturitas cuyos enemigos acabaran encontrandose con los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo lo ha vuelto a hacer. Ademas, esta vez ha sido delante de Papa Pitufo. Ha pronunciado un hechizo que convierte todo en piedra. Todo, incluyendo a el mismo y a los demas Pitufos, asi como la aldea y muchos kilometros del bosque que hay alrededor. Afortunadamente, aparece Guillermo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Antes, en la Aldea Pitufa no habia reloj. Sin embargo, el tiempo se ha convertido de repente en algo precioso, y Pitufo Vanidoso elabora un plan para aprovecharse del nuevo reloj de la aldea. ¿Podran sobrevivir los Pitufos al ataque del tiempo?

programme.title: El Pitufo Vanidoso
programme.desc: El espejo magico de Gargamel deja atrapado a Pitufo Vanidoso dentro de el, asi que Pitufina y Pitufo Filosofo se apresuran para rescatarlo. Una vez estan dentro del mundo del espejo, provocan una gran explosion que rompe el cristal del espejo, pudiendo volver sanos y salvos al pueblo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Deshollinador se encarga de limpiar las chimeneas y no es precisamente el habitante mas popular de la Aldea Pitufa. Es bastante desalinado, y las nubes de hollin que suelta no contribuyen a aumentar su popularidad. Unicamente los Pitufitos le consideran una excelente compania, ya que es el unico Pitufo que puede ensuciarse sin que le rinan. Sin embargo, el entusiasmo de los Pitufitos por Pitufo Deshollinador pone en peligro la aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El futbol (o pitufutbol, como ellos lo llaman) es un pasatiempo que esta bien para un rato. Sin embargo, se vuelve aburrido despues de algunos siglos. Ahora hay un nuevo juego, inventado por uno de los Pitufos: un juego en el que golpeas una bola con un palo y lo tienes que introducir en un agujero de topo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El Pitufidia de la Amistad es el momento del ano en el que, mas que nunca, los Pitufos demuestran su amabilidad con los demas. ¿Conseguira Clorhidris destruir esos buenos sentimientos? ¿Y como pueden los Pitufos encontrar una forma de cambiar las flechas de Cupido por algo mas agradable?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Natural y Travieso roban la formula de Gargamel para hacer otro Pitufo - otra pitufa para acompanar a Pitufina. Asi pues, crean a Sassette, que crea problemas por doquier. Haciendo uso de su pocion, Papa Pitufo convierte la malvada creacion de Gargamel en una simpatica Sassette.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Te despiertas temprano por la manana, antes de que los demas Pitufos se hayan levantado de sus camas, para preparar sabrosos bizcochos de pitufrutas. Dedicas toda la manana a preparar pitufimanjares para el almuerzo. Despues, toda la tarde a tener la deliciosa cena lista a tiempo. ¿Y acaso los demas Pitufos te dan siquiera las gracias? Asi pues, Pitufo Goloso renuncia. La aldea esta en problemas... y pronto, tambien lo esta Pitufo Goloso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos intentan evitar el contacto con los humanos. Esta vez, sin embargo, Sasita se ha hecho amiga de una pequena bruja llamada Melina, cuyos hechizos suelen acabar en desastre. De todas formas, ¿son las brujas realmente humanas? En cualquier caso, los brujos como Gargamel si que lo son.

programme.title: Secreto Del Pozo De La Aldea
programme.desc: ¿Por que Pitufo Torpe espera dia y noche junto al pozo de la aldea? ¿Cual es el deseo que quiere mantener en secreto? ¿Y como esta involucrado Gargamel en este asunto misterioso? ¿Lograra Gargamel atrapar por fin a los Pitufos?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Armonia La Estrella De La Funcion
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia firma inconscientemente un contrato con Escritor Fantasma para escribir una sinfonia, lo que hace que quede atrapado en un club nocturno fantasmal para siempre. Papa Pitufo exige un juicio con un jurado y un juez de fantasmas, que declaran inocente a Pitufo Armonia y culpable de plagio a Escritor Fantasma.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador vera cumplido su deseo de ser un Astropitufo cuando Papa Pitufo le hechiza para quedarse dormido, transformando el paisaje y a los Pitufos en una fantasia galactica. Gargamel vigila de cerca las travesuras de los Pitufos desde su bola de cristal, pero el hechizo de Papa Pitufo tambien tiene efecto en el y le transporta hasta el centro de una tormenta.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La produccion teatral de los Pitufos "Pitufo Robin" se convierte en realidad con un actor real del legendario heroe.

programme.title: BRUCE LI: DEADLY STRIKE - Desafio con la Muerte
programme.desc: El nuevo jefe de policía (Bruce Li) llega a una pequeña ciudad de provincias. Ha sido acusado de llevar ante la justicia a una peligrosa pandilla. Pero en cuestión de segundos, el jefe provoca un enfrentamiento con sus perezosos ayudantes. El grupo, tanto prisioneros como policías, finalmente se une y rastrea la sede de la pandilla para encontrar al líder (Chen Hsing). Después de una pelea larga y sangrienta, todos yacen muertos excepto el jefe.

programme.title: MISSION THUNDERBOLT - Trueno Mision
programme.desc: El Magnate Blanco contrata a unos sicarios internacionales para que enfrenten a dos poderosas pandillas de Hong Kong, de modo que su organización pueda controlar la región. Esta película es una pesadilla de intriga y engaño.

programme.title: BUDDHA ASSASSINATOR - El Saludo del Buda
programme.desc: Lord Tsoi of the Manchus es emboscado por los luchadores por la libertad Ming. El fanático del kung fu, Shao Hai, lo rescata. Shao Hai pronto descubre que le han ordenado matar a un miembro de su propia familia, por lo que el joven vengador se venga. Surge un enfrentamiento épico.

programme.title: SUPER DRAGONS DYNAMO - El dinamismo del dragon
programme.desc: Magnate, Tang Shih Hai, gobierna la mayoría de los negocios en Hong Kong. Muchos de sus funcionarios han sido asesinados. Como el único hijo de Tang, Champ, es vago, Tang nombra a Cheng como su gerente general, sin saber que es miembro del temido ICG (Grupo Criminal Internacional).

programme.title: SHAOLIN INVINCIBLE STICKS - Los Bastones Invencibles de Shaolin
programme.desc: Lee Tso Nam, dirige esta magnífica película de acción de artes marciales. - La gran estrella del kung fu Wong Tao aparece en la película como el futuro líder del Clan de los Palos Invencibles. El Luchador del Asta que Parte el Aire (Chang Yi), se opone a su búsqueda del control del grupo. Sus épicos duelos constituyen la mayor parte de esta película.

programme.title: Ella es Ramona
programme.desc: Ramona is a fat woman with too much weight and barely any luck, her universe seems to be collapsing after a series of unfortunate events. But everything will soon get better thanks to some magical beetles she finds in a Tarot café.

programme.title: Por la libre
programme.desc: Rodri y Rocco son dos jóvenes primos. Ambos coinciden en la fiesta de cumpleaños de su abuelo, un gran viejo español con quien tienen una relación que nunca han podido establecer con sus respectivos padres. El abuelo se ha convertido en su confesor - incondicional. Desgraciadamente muere y su última voluntad es que esparzan sus cenizas en - Acapulco.

programme.title: El viaje de la nonna
programme.desc: A Mexican family, wanting to grant their Grandmother her last wish, embarks on a make believe trip to a small town in Italy ... in Mexico!

programme.title: El segundo aire
programme.desc: Julia mantiene una relación secreta con su alumno Ricardo. Moisés, su marido, le provoca un accidente y no les queda más remedio que llevarse al joven a su casa hasta que se recupere.

programme.title: La última noticia
programme.desc: A Peruvian radio host risks his life to report on clashes between police and militant guerrillas.

programme.title: Día naranja
programme.desc: Three beautiful women from different cities in Latin America. Ana, in Buenos Aires; Sol, in Bogota and Patricia in Caracas, go through a day in which they are simultaneously faced with the same challenge: an unexpected pregnancy.

programme.title: Recuperando a mi ex
programme.desc: A retired couple will have to defend their home against an unpredicted menace: Their kids moving back.

programme.title: Timbiriche: la misma piedra
programme.desc: Una divertida y emotiva mirada al último reencuentro del mítico grupo TIMBIRICHE. Los ensayos, los conciertos, el reality show, los problemas, las juntas y los hijos. Retratados a lo largo de un año y medio de una manera ágil e íntima, como nunca se les había visto. Un testimonio imperdible para toda una generación que creció junto con ellos cantando y bailando sus canciones de los 80's. Y para los nuevos fans que recién los descubrieron en los más de 80 shows de la gira de festejo por los 25 años de su creación.

programme.title: Perros del fin del mundo
programme.desc: Perros del Fin del mundo is a documentary that establishes a portrait of a threat that stalks Tierra del Fuego, its people and its culture. How a harmless and adorable pet, when it is abandoned by the irresponsible possession of man, recovers its wild state and approaches the behaviors of her ancestors, the wolves. And about what man does with this new reality that he created.

programme.title: Paraguay, droga y banana
programme.desc: A thrilling, incisive documentary that breaks down how a prominent drug trafficker’s settlement in Paraguay in the late ’60s set in motion a wave of rampant corruption, leaving no part of the country untouched.

programme.title: Tamara y la catarina
programme.desc: Narra la travesía de dos mujeres que se desdibujan en su soledad e invisibilidad y que tendrán que convivir más allá de lo que esperaban, y encontrar una en la otra un espacio donde no son parias, donde son necesitadas. Es una historia en la que los personajes irán descubriendo, en sus errores y su condición, una forma de existir entre ellas

programme.title: Soles negros
programme.desc: México se ha transformado en una gigantesca fosa común, debido al clima de impunidad establecido tanto por las bandas criminales como por las autoridades estatales.

programme.title: El mariachi gringo
programme.desc: A stifled, small-town man stuck in a dead end life, runs away to Mexico to be a mariachi singer. MARIACHI GRINGO is a musical tour-de-force exploring the reality of "following your dreams" across cultural, personal, social and geographical borders.

programme.title: Lo que le pasó a Sansón
programme.desc: El vago Tin Tan y su celosa novia, la peinadora Lila, van al cine a ver "Sansón y Dalila". De regreso a casa Tin Tan sueña con que él es Sansón y Lila es Dalila. En el sueño, Sansón tiene amores con Miriam, pero cae hechizado por la belleza de Dalila, quien le roba la fuerza al cortarle el cabello. Sansón recupera su fuerza y se enfrenta al príncipe Arthur.

programme.title: Rosario
programme.desc: Rosario y Carlos, esposos, forman parte parte de una compañía de teatro. En una escena de celos, ella debe disparar y matarlo. Carlos ha tenido una aventura con Zulma, otra actriz de la compañía, lo que no ha ocultado. La normalidad vuelve al matrimonio, y ese mismo día en la escena final del drama que representaban Rosario y Carlos, ella mata accidentalmente a su marido. Alguien cambio la pistola....
